filters : 

We can think of a filter as a transformer,
a program that transforms input data into output data.
There are many examples, including wc, cat, more head, sort, grep and so on. 

pipe :

for chining filter commands.
--------------------------------

defining shell variable : 

$ GREETING = "Hello"
$ echo $GREETING
Hello

unset GREETING                 -- DELETE THE greeting variable value
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Enviroment variable

.extended var_name

.env- list all enviroment variables

summary : 

filters are shell commands.
The pipe operator ' | ' allows you to chain filter commands.
Shell variables can be assigned values with '=' and listed using set.
Environment variables are shell variables with scope extended to all
child processes of the shell. 
